column10: American Indian or Alaska Native % of Cases
column11: American Indian or Alaska Native % of Total Population

column13: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander % of Total Population

column1: Source: KFF analysis of Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, COVID-19 Response. COVID-19 Case Surveillance Restricted Data Access, Summary, and Limitations. Total State Population Distribution by Race/Ethnicity based on KFF analysis of 2019 American Community Survey.
*NR*: Data not reported due to more than 50% of cases with unknown race/ethnicity.
*NA*: Data suppressed when fewer than 10 cases occur.
Percent of cases in each state may not sum to 100% due to rounding. Percentages are based on a total of all probable and confirmed cases for which race/ethnicity is known.

% of Cases Missing Race/Ethnicity Data is the share of total cases reported in a state for which race/ethnicity is not known. Some states do not update race/ethnicity information as frequently as the count of total cases for that state, which may increase the % of Cases Missing Race/Ethnicity Data.
Persons of Hispanic origin may be of any race.
As of April 19, 2021, data on COVID-19 cases is from CDC COVID-19 Case Surveillance Restricted Data. Data prior to April 19 was from The COVID Tracking Project, COVID Racial Data Tracker.
The CDC does not take responsibility for the scientific validity or accuracy of methodology, results, statistical analyses, or conclusions presented.
